The '''91st Mobile Reconnaissance Corps''', also identified as the '''91st Mobile Reconnaissance Force''', the '''91st Expeditionary Corps''', or simply as the '''91st Recon Corps''', was a [[clone trooper]] [[corps]] in the [[Grand Army of the Republic]]. During the [[Clone Wars]], a pan-[[The galaxy|galactic]] conflict between the [[Galactic Republic]] and [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]], the 91st was placed under the command of [[Jedi General]] [[Adi Gallia]] and [[Clone Marshal Commander]] [[Neyo]]. Throughout the war, Jedi General [[Mace Windu]] was also in command of the corps, with Jedi Generals [[Oppo Rancisis]] and [[Stass Allie]] taking command during the [[Siege of Saleucami]] and its aftermath. Following the [[Proclamation of the New Order|transformation]] of the Galactic Republic into the [[Galactic Empire]] and the commencement of the [[Great Jedi Purge]], the 91st Mobile Reconnaissance Corps was reorganized under the new [[Imperial Army]].

==Characteristics==
===Organization===
[[File:91st-Corps-Specialist.png|thumb|left|304x304px|A clone sharpshooter of the 91st Mobile Recon Corps.]]
The 91st Mobile Reconnaissance Corps,<ref name="SWHC1" /> also identified as the 91st Mobile Reconnaissance Force,<ref name="Join the Battle">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Character Encyclopedia - Join the Battle!]]''</ref> or as the 91st Expeditionary Corps,<ref name="BC 42">{{BustCollectionCite|42|Character}}</ref> was a [[corps]] in the [[Grand Army of the Republic]],<ref name="SWHC1" /> and as such consisted of 36,864 [[trooper]]s divided into sixteen [[regiment]]s.<ref name="Complete Locations">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']] establishes that a [[corps]] in the [[Grand Army of the Republic]] contains 36,864 [[clone trooper]]s divided into sixteen [[regiment]]s. Since the 91st Mobile Reconnaissance Corps is a corps within the Grand Army, it must have 36,864 troopers divided into sixteen regiments.</ref> It contained [[Lightning Squadron]], a specialized<ref name="BC 42" /> [[Tank|armored]] [[cavalry]] [[squadron]] of [[Advanced Recon Force trooper|Advanced Recon Force Scout Troopers]].<ref name="Liberty" /> The 91st's [[clone trooper]]s also consisted of [[Biker Advanced Recon Commando]]s<ref name="Episode III" /> as well as standard troopers,<ref name="Nomad Droids" /> [[clone sharpshooter]]s, [[clone trooper officer]]s, and [[heavy weapons clone trooper]]s.<ref name="Battlefront II" />

The 91st Mobile Reconnaissance Corps was under the leadership of [[Jedi General]] [[Adi Gallia]],<ref name="Nomad Droids" /> though [[Master of the Order]] [[General]] [[Mace Windu]] led at least parts of it during the [[Battle of Ryloth]].<ref name="Liberty on Ryloth">{{TCW|Liberty on Ryloth}}</ref> During the [[Siege of Saleucami]], the 91st was temporarily placed under the command of Council member Jedi General [[Oppo Rancisis]], and once the siege was finished, Jedi General [[Stass Allie]] took command of the 91st to clear out any pockets of resistance. The 91st's commanding clone officer was [[Clone Marshal Commander]] [[Neyo]], who was placed in command following his promotion earlier in the [[Clone Wars]].<ref name="GAR">{{EncyclopediaCite|The Grand Army of the Republic}}</ref>

===Equipment and vehicles===
[[File:91st_Recon_Corps.jpg|thumb|left|300px|91st Biker Advanced Recon Commandos on patrol aboard BARC speeders]]
The 91st Recon Corps standard [[clone trooper]]s of the corps had deep [[Color|red]] markings and characteristic mark on their armor. Standard [[clone trooper]]s made use of the [[Phase I clone trooper armor]], [[Advanced Recon Force trooper|ARF trooper]] armor, and later [[Phase II clone trooper armor]] and phase II [[Biker Advanced Recon Commando|BARC trooper]] armor. Soldiers of the 91st Recon Corps were typically equipped with [[DC-15A blaster carbine|DC-15A blasters]].<ref name="GAR" />

The 91st Recon Corps used a variety of vehicles. The corps' aerial component consisted of LAAT/i [[gunship]]s. Ground vehicles consisted of walkers such as [[All Terrain Tactical Enforcer]]s, [[All Terrain Reconnaissance Transport]]s and [[BARC speeder]]s.<ref name="Liberty" /> At times, members of the 91st Recon Corps were present aboard the [[Venator-class Star Destroyer|''Venator''-class Star Destroyer]] ''[[Endurance]]''.<ref name="Death Trap">{{TCW|Death Trap}}</ref> The corps also rode on [[blurrg]], native [[Species|beasts]] of Ryloth, when they assaulted the planet's capital city of Lessu.<ref name="Liberty" />

==History==
===Clone Wars===
====Battle for Ryloth====
The 91st Mobile Recon Corps was part of the [[Grand Army of the Republic]] and fought in the [[Clone Wars]] between the [[Galactic Republic]] and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Separatist Alliance]], with the [[clone trooper]]s under the unit considering themselves to be elite [[soldier]]s.<ref name="91st Recon FC" />

Early during the war, the 91st participated in the [[Battle of Ryloth]], when [[Jedi General]] [[Mace Windu]], alongside [[Clone Commander]] [[Ponds]], led their forces to attempt to liberate the capital of [[Lessu City]]. En route to [[Ryloth]]'s capital city on a cliff, General Windu's [[Tank|armored]] forces came under attack by a group of [[Armored Assault Tank Mk I|Armored Assault Tanks]] while traversing a road alongside a mountain. The contingent of Separatist Alliance forces were able to stop the Republic troops briefly, but were defeated by [[Lightning Squadron]], which were deployed from the [[All Terrain Tactical Enforcer|AT-TEs]] of the 91st. After that skirmish, Windu, [[Stak]], and [[Razor]] came across [[General]] [[Cham Syndulla]] of the [[Twi'lek Resistance]] and his men after they took out a droid patrol. At first, Syndulla was hesitant to join Windu due to another possible occupation by the Republic, but when he learned that the Separatists were bombing [[Twi'lek]] villages with [[Hyena-class Droid Fighter/Bomber|''Hyena''-class Droid Bombers]], Syndulla decided to help the Republic.<ref name="Liberty" />

Reaching Lessu, Windu and the two [[Advanced Recon Force trooper|ARF troopers]] then hid inside an [[Multi-Troop Transport|MTTs]] that was part of a [[convoy]] entering the city. Windu then ordered Syndulla and [[Commander]] Ponds to commence the attack after [[Bridge (starship)|bridge]] was on. The [[battle droid]]s scanned the cargo on the bridge, and they discovered Windu and his men. After he subdued the droids, Windu pushed his troopers across the bridge as it was being turned off by the droids. As he fell, Windu was able to jump on one of the [[Single Trooper Aerial Platform|STAPs]] and get to other side of the bridge. Windu then held off the droids as Stak and Razor made their way to the control room. After destroying droids in control room They were then able to turn the bridge on and hold it against a few droid reinforcements, including a pair of [[BX-series droid commando|commando droids]]. Syndulla and his men fought the battle droids as Windu went to capture Separatist [[Emir]] [[Wat Tambor]], liberating Lessu.<ref name="Liberty" />

====Battles on Saleucami and Malastare====
At some point after the Battle of Ryloth, the 91st [[Battle of Saleucami (Mekedrix)|fought]] on<ref name="Obi-Wan 4">[[Obi-Wan 4|''Obi-Wan'' 4]]</ref> the planet<ref name="Neyo">{{Databank|clone-commander-neyo|Clone Commander Neyo}}</ref> [[Saleucami]]. Fighting alongside [[Commander]] [[Mekedrix]]<ref name="Obi-Wan 4" /> of [[Roon's military defense forces]],<ref name="Obi-Wan 3">[[Obi-Wan 3|''Obi-Wan'' 3]]</ref> three clones from the 91st, one of them an officer, rode BARC speeders as part of the engagement.<ref name="Obi-Wan 4" />

The Confederacy's efforts on the [[planet]] [[Malastare]] were successful, so [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] ordered the use of an [[electro-proton bomb]] to deactivate the Separatists' [[Separatist Droid Army|droid army]]. The [[bomb]] worked, but had the unforeseen effect of creating a sinkhole. Windu, alongside Ponds and troopers; "[[Hawkeye]]" and "[[Trapper (clone trooper)|Trapper]]" discovered the [[Zillo Beast]].<ref name="Zillo Beast">{{TCW|The Zillo Beast}}</ref>

====Crisis on ''Endurance''====
After the Battle on Malastare young [[Boba Fett]] infiltrate Windu's [[Venator-class Star Destroyer|''Venator''-class Star Destroyer]] ''[[Endurance]]''. Fett didn't kill Windu but he crushed the ship on planet [[Vanqor]]. Most of the crew evacuated, but Fett, with help of the [[Aurra Sing]], [[Bossk'wassak'Cradossk|Bossk]] and [[Castas]], captured [[Admiral]] [[Shoan Kilian]], Commander Ponds and a [[Unidentified clone navigation officer (Endurance)|clone naval officer]]. Shortly after this, Ponds was executed by Aurra Sing.<ref name="Lethal Trackdown">{{TCW|Lethal Trackdown}}</ref>

====Battle of Patitie Pattuna====
Later in the war Gallia's Jedi cruiser was attacked by a Separatist fleet under the command of General [[Grievous]]. Gallia and her troops battled the [[cyborg]] when he boarded her [[cruiser]], putting up a good fight but she was ultimately defeated and captured. Later she watched as Grievous attacked a [[Marauder (Weequay pirate ship)|pirate ship]]. Gallia was soon rescued by [[Plo Koon]], "Wolffe," and the [[104th Battalion]]; again, Grievous escaped before he could be taken into custody.<ref name="Nomad Droids" />

====D-Squad====
In [[20 BBY]],<ref name="Timelines">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> [[Cloning|Clone]] Commander [[Neyo]]'s [[DUM-series pit droid]], [[WAC-47]], transferred from the 91st to [[Colonel]] [[Meebur Gascon]]'s [[D-Squad]].<ref name="WACdata" /> The droid [[squad]] later saved high-[[Military rank|ranking]] members of the [[Republic Military]] echelon, including Neyo, from a [[Carida incident|Separatist attack]] on the [[Valor (space station)|''Valor'']] [[space station]].<ref name="PONR">{{TCW|Point of No Return (The Clone Wars)}}</ref>

====Siege of Saleucami====
[[File:StassAllieDeath.jpg|thumb|325px|Commander Neyo executing Order 66 on Stass Allie]]
Just as they had earlier in the war,<ref name="Obi-Wan 4" /> the 91st was deployed to Saleucami during the [[Outer Rim Sieges]].<ref name="Neyo" /> After the Republic claimed victory, [[General]] [[Stass Allie]], Neyo, and another [[Unidentified clone lieutenant|clone lieutenant]] patrolled the battlefield afterward. At that moment, Supreme Chancellor Palpatine triggered [[Order 66]], causing clone [[trooper]]s across [[the galaxy]] to betray and [[Death|kill]] their [[Jedi]] leaders.<ref name="Episode III" /> As a result, Allie was [[Great Jedi Purge|executed]] by Neyo and the other clone while on a [[BARC speeder|speeder bike]] patrol.<ref name="Neyo" />

===Under the Empire===
After Order 66 and the [[Proclamation of the New Order|transformation]] of the Republic into the [[Galactic Empire]],<ref name="Episode III" /> the 91st Recon Corps continued to serve in its [[Imperial Army|ground forces]] and actively fought for the new regime.<ref name="91st Recon FC" />

